The program seems to be swapping the arguments when calling `encodeScore`, 
so let's switch that. The corrected Tundra code should look like this:

```tundra
def encodeScore(base, adjustment) {
  return base * 10 + adjustment;
}

val raw = {
  base: "7",
  adjustment: "3"
};

val base = parseNumber(raw.base);
val adjustment = parseNumber(raw.adjustment);
val code = encodeScore(base, adjustment);

print(code);
```

This will now correctly calculate `encodeScore` as if it were a score codin
coding system where the base number (7 in this case) is multiplied by 10 an
and then added to the adjustment value (3 in this case). The result of the 
calculation should be printed out, producing "73".
